## ğŸ³ Docker Implementation

### Dockerfile (Production Ready)

* Multi-stage compatible
* Builds React app inside container
* Eliminates Node.js dependency on Jenkins agent

```

### Local Validation

```bash
docker build -t trend-app .
docker run -p 3000:3000 trend-app
```

---

## ğŸ” Jenkins CI/CD Pipeline (Final & Stable)

### Key Design Decisions

* **Pipeline script from SCM** (not inline)
* **checkout scm** used correctly
* Credentials handled securely
* Docker build performed inside pipeline
* Kubernetes deploy via kubeconfig

### Jenkinsfile (Declarative)
Jenkins declarative file for SCM pipeline execution

## ğŸ” Jenkins Credentials (Critical)

| Credential ID   | Type              | Purpose                 |
| --------------- | ----------------- | ----------------------- |
| dockerhub-creds | Username/Password | Push image to DockerHub |
| kubeconfig      |                   | Access AWS EKS cluster  |

âš ï¸ Credentials **must exist in the same job/folder scope** as the pipeline.

---

## â˜ï¸ Terraform â€“ AWS EKS (Module-Based)

* No CLI-based EKS creation
* Uses official Terraform AWS EKS module
* Creates VPC, subnets, node groups, IAM roles

### Provisioning

```bash
cd terraform
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

---

## â˜¸ï¸ Kubernetes Deployment

### deployment.yml

* 2 replicas
* Uses DockerHub image
* Rolling updates enabled

### service.yml

* Type: LoadBalancer
* Exposes app publicly

```bash
kubectl apply -f deployment.yml
kubectl apply -f service.yml
kubectl get svc trend-service

```

---

## ğŸŒ Application Access

Once deployed, access the app using:

```
http://<EXTERNAL-LOADBALANCER-IP>
```

(ARN/DNS captured as part of submission)

